    &lt;CommentText&gt;Can't believe I had to wait 9 hours in SAU sat in a chair after being sent there by my GP it took over 4 hours to even be seen by someone, apparently others there had been waiting for over 12 1/2 hours. Totally unacceptable there were only about 12 patients there but no one was being dealt with, even when you were seen by a doctor you then had to wait about 4 hours before their requests were actioned (in my case having an x-ray taken),I got to dept at 5pm and didn't leave until 2.30am, I was assured by registrar  I would be phoned this morning with a CT scan slot for today, when I rang them this morning Dr told me no Dr should promise CT scan next day and that they'd get back to me, when had no call back phoned again and finally got scan for 10th March&lt;/CommentText&gt;
